                            <comment id="16047007" author="sseth" created="Mon, 12 Jun 2017 20:09:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. I&apos;d still change the isShutdown to a volatile, before commit, for the one opportunistic check to be more consistent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16047313" author="sershe" created="Tue, 13 Jun 2017 01:38:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to master after making the change. Thanks for the review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16110071" author="mithun" created="Wed, 2 Aug 2017 00:51:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;sershe&lt;/a&gt;, I wonder if a similar fix should go into &lt;tt&gt;MergeFileTask::execute()&lt;/tt&gt;, to check for cancellation before job-submission. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16111429" author="sershe" created="Wed, 2 Aug 2017 17:59:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;MergeFileTask doesn&apos;t appear to implement shutdown at all. So, execute is safe from interference &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16111648" author="mithun" created="Wed, 2 Aug 2017 20:06:22 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;MergeFileTask doesn&apos;t appear to implement shutdown at all.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;:] Ah, but doesn&apos;t it need one? It is conceivable that a user might cancel a query between the TezTask and the MergeFileTask, (or simply interrupt an &lt;tt&gt;ALTER TABLE CONCATENATE&lt;/tt&gt;). In that case, the merge will run through to the end, in spite of cancellation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder if there isn&apos;t value in applying the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12556&quot; title=&quot;Ctrl-C in beeline doesn&amp;#39;t kill Tez query on HS2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-12556&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-12556&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; + &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-16820&quot; title=&quot;TezTask may not shut down correctly before submit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-16820&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-16820&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; treatment for MergeFileTask as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16111755" author="sershe" created="Wed, 2 Aug 2017 21:30:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, what I was saying is that we don&apos;t need the same bugfix for that task cause there&apos;s no implementation. It probably does need an implementation (without bugs like this).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16113354" author="mithun" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2017 19:35:24 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yeah, what I was saying is that we don&apos;t need the same bugfix for that task ...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Right. Sorry, I didn&apos;t mean to imply otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It probably does need an implementation (without bugs like this).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m working on it. Our fix for this was not as complete/correct as yours. I&apos;ll extend this for &lt;tt&gt;MergeFileTask&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16113361" author="sershe" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2017 19:38:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! I&apos;d be happy to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16119041" author="mithun" created="Tue, 8 Aug 2017 21:10:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-17273&quot; title=&quot;MergeFileTask needs to be interruptible&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-17273&quot;&gt;HIVE-17273&lt;/a&gt; for extending this to &lt;tt&gt;MergeFileTask&lt;/tt&gt;, so that I don&apos;t drop the ball on this. Thanks, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;sershe&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16486417" author="vgarg" created="Wed, 23 May 2018 00:00:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hive 3.0.0 has been released so closing this jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
